--- [DEBUG] NARRATION LLM OUTPUT ---
Vacuum tubes were the fundamental building blocks of early computers, acting like tiny electronic switches that controlled the flow of electricity to represent data and perform calculations. Their ability to amplify signals made complex processing possible, but they were large, fragile, and generated a lot of heat. Despite these challenges, vacuum tubes powered the first generation of computers, laying the groundwork for all modern computing technology.
